1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,880
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,880 --> 00:00:04,880
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:08,840
My name is Kathryn and we have an unusual lesson for you today.
我是Kathryn，今天我们有一节不同寻常的课程。

4
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:11,760
It's more about writing than about speaking.
这节课更多是关于写作，而不是口语。

5
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:12,760
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:17,680
Well, many times we have to write emails and if we're working in a sales environment, we
嗯，很多时候我们都需要写邮件，如果我们在销售环境中工作，

7
00:00:17,680 --> 00:00:20,680
may need to write an email to a potential client.
可能需要给潜在客户写一封邮件。

8
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:25,560
Alright, so we're going to learn what is appropriate and what is not in today's lesson.
好的，所以在今天的课程中，我们将学习什么是合适的，什么是不合适的。

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:28,520
Let's take a listen to our dialogue.
让我们来听一下我们的对话。

10
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:36,640
Melanie, can you help me with something?
Melanie，你能帮我个忙吗？

11
00:00:36,640 --> 00:00:41,400
We need to finalize the account with the Mexican embassy and I need some advice on phrasing
我们需要敲定与墨西哥大使馆的账户，我需要一些关于如何用英语正确措辞这封信的建议。

12
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:44,120
this letter correctly in English.
这封信。

13
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:50,000
Sure Tracy, let me just get my laptop.
当然，Tracy，让我拿一下我的笔记本电脑。

14
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:56,760
Right, all set.
好了，准备好了。

15
00:00:56,760 --> 00:01:01,840
Ok, so, to whom it may concern, I am writing…
好的，那么，敬启者，我写信是为了……

16
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:05,760
Um, Tracy, I think that's a little too formal.
嗯，Tracy，我觉得这有点太正式了。

17
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:10,440
I know you want to be polite, but you've already made contact with them, so in English,
我知道你想表现得礼貌，但你已经和他们联系过了，所以在英语中，

18
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:12,880
you can be a bit more relaxed in the opening.
开头可以稍微放松一点。

19
00:01:12,880 --> 00:01:14,720
Ok, more relaxed.
好的，更放松一点。

20
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,720
Got it.
明白了。

21
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,280
Hey Sally, what's up?
嘿，Sally，最近怎么样？

22
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:19,240
It's Tracy here, just…
我是Tracy，只是……

23
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:23,160
Ok, Tracy, now it's too relaxed.
好了，Tracy，现在又太随意了。

24
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:25,320
You've still got to show some respect.
你还是得表现出一些尊重。

25
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:28,880
How about starting with Dear Miss Cooper, I'm writing to confirm…
不如以“亲爱的Cooper小姐，我写信是为了确认……”开头？

26
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,760
Great, ok.
太好了，好的。

27
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:39,240
Dear Miss Cooper, I'm writing to confirm the final quotation for the full-page back
亲爱的Cooper小姐，我写信是为了确认您为《Viola》杂志春季刊要求的全页封底彩色广告的最终报价。

28
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:48,360
cover color advertisement you requested for the spring issue of Viola Magazine.
全页封底彩色广告。

29
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,720
That's great.
太好了。

30
00:01:49,720 --> 00:02:00,560
The final costing, including advert design and production, comes to 45,600 RMB.
最终成本，包括广告设计和制作，共计45,600元人民币。

31
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:08,080
We want payment 10 working days before publication, or we will cancel the ad.
我们要求在出版前10个工作日付款，否则我们将取消广告。

32
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,480
Thanks for…
感谢……

33
00:02:09,480 --> 00:02:12,320
Whoa, ok, back up a second Tracy.
哇，好的，Tracy，先停一下。

34
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:14,420
That's too direct.
这太直接了。

35
00:02:14,420 --> 00:02:19,800
Can I suggest you say, please note that the final payment is due two working weeks before
我建议你说，请注意，最终付款应在出版前两个工作周内支付。

36
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,800
publication.
支付。

37
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,800
You don't want to offend her.
你不想冒犯她。

38
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,920
Oops, ok, you're right.
哎呀，好的，你说得对。

39
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:28,280
Then I can just end with, all the best, Tracy.
那我就可以以“此致敬礼，Tracy”结尾。

40
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:33,680
Hmm, maybe I'd play it safe and just finish with, yours sincerely.
嗯，也许我会稳妥一点，就以“您真诚的”结尾。

41
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,680
That's more professional.
那样更专业。

42
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:37,560
Oh, Melanie, you're a lifesaver.
哦，Melanie，你真是我的救星。

43
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,560
Thank you.
谢谢你。

44
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:47,200
Alright, we're back, so now let's take a look at some of that vocab we heard on
好了，我们回来了，现在让我们看看在“语言要点”中听到的一些词汇。

45
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:51,200
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

46
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,940
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

47
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:56,040
We have some wonderful adjectives today.
今天我们有一些很棒的形容词。

48
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:59,320
The first one that I wanted to discuss, Marco, is formal.
我想讨论的第一个词，Marco，是“正式”。

49
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,840
Formal, that's right.
“正式”，没错。

50
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:04,400
We want to be a little bit more formal when we're writing someone we don't really know
当我们给不太熟悉的人写信时，我们想表现得稍微正式一点。

51
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:05,400
too much.
不太熟悉的人。

52
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,400
That's right.
没错。

53
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,960
But be careful because sometimes you can be too formal.
但要小心，因为有时你可能太正式了。

54
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,040
So what exactly does formal mean?
那么“正式”到底是什么意思呢？

55
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:16,720
So if you write a formal email, it's very proper, very respectful.
如果你写一封正式的邮件，它非常得体，非常尊重。

56
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:24,000
So proper in the way that you wouldn't use colloquial terms or phrasal verbs that you
得体是指你不会使用和朋友们说话时用的口语化词汇或短语动词。

57
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,000
would use with your friends.
口语化词汇或短语动词。

58
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:30,440
No, a good example is writing to a lawyer or a judge.
不，一个很好的例子是给律师或法官写信。

59
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:32,840
You want to use formal language.
你想使用正式的语言。

60
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,800
Even with a teacher, you might use more formal language.
即使是对老师，你也可能使用更正式的语言。

61
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,720
But with a friend, you don't have to.
但对朋友，你就不必这样。

62
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,720
That's something else.
那是另一回事。

63
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:39,720
That's right.
没错。

64
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,600
So when you're writing something that's formal, it's important to be polite as well.
所以当你写正式的东西时，保持礼貌也很重要。

65
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,600
Now what is polite?
那么什么是“礼貌”呢？

66
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,600
Right.
对。

67
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:48,960
So you want to be formal, you want to be serious, and you want to be polite.
所以你想表现得正式、严肃，并且想表现得礼貌。

68
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,680
You want to show respect.
你想表现出尊重。

69
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:53,220
You want to be nice, basically.
基本上，你想表现得友善。

70
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,220
That's right.
没错。

71
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:56,680
And so people can often be described as polite.
人们经常可以被描述为有礼貌。

72
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:59,760
He's very polite or she's not polite at all.
他很有礼貌，或者她一点也不礼貌。

73
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:03,520
And when I was a little kid, my mom used to say, it's very important to be polite.
我小时候，我妈妈常说，有礼貌非常重要。

74
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:07,160
You say thank you and you're welcome when you're talking to other people.
和别人说话时要说“谢谢”和“不客气”。

75
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,160
That's right.
没错。

76
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,120
And that's one way of being polite.
这是有礼貌的一种方式。

77
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:15,520
Now also when we are describing the way that you speak to someone or the way that you write,
另外，当我们描述你说话或写作的方式时，

78
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,560
you can be very direct.
你可以非常“直接”。

79
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:22,000
Now being direct means that you say exactly what you want or exactly what you're thinking.
“直接”意味着你准确地说出你想要什么或你在想什么。

80
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:27,080
Okay, so maybe if we're talking to this company, you say, hi, I want this.
好的，所以如果我们和这家公司谈话，你说，嗨，我想要这个。

81
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,360
I will pay this much.
我会付这么多钱。

82
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,360
Thank you.
谢谢。

83
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,360
Bye.
再见。

84
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,360
Right.
对。

85
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,360
That's maybe too direct.
那可能太直接了。

86
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:36,800
You need to be a little less direct and say nice things in an email.
你需要稍微委婉一点，在邮件里说些好话。

87
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,800
That's right.
没错。

88
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:42,680
So maybe you want to say to someone that you don't really like the clothes they're wearing,
所以，比如你想对某人说，你不太喜欢他们穿的衣服，

89
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:43,680
right?
对吧？

90
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,280
You say, hey, do you like my new shirt?
你说，嘿，你喜欢我的新衬衫吗？

91
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:48,040
And if you're very direct, you would say, no, I think it's very ugly.
如果你很直接，你会说，不，我觉得它很丑。

92
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,040
I hate it.
我讨厌它。

93
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,040
Right.
对。

94
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,040
That's too direct.
那太直接了。

95
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:55,440
So maybe you would say, I don't really think it suits you very well.
所以也许你会说，我不太觉得它很适合你。

96
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:58,200
Or I think a different color would be better on you.
或者，我觉得换个颜色会更好看。

97
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,200
That's right.
没错。

98
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:01,440
So that's being a little bit less direct.
所以这就是稍微委婉一点。

99
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:06,600
Now obviously, if you're too direct with someone, you may offend that person.
现在，显然，如果你对某人太直接，你可能会冒犯到那个人。

100
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:11,920
Alright, to offend is a verb and to offend someone means to say something that makes
好的，“冒犯”是一个动词，冒犯某人意味着说一些让他们

101
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,500
them unhappy or upset or even angry.
不开心、难过甚至生气的话。

102
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:20,240
So going back to the same example of the shirt, if you say, I think that shirt is very ugly,
所以回到衬衫的例子，如果你说，我觉得那件衬衫很丑，

103
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,000
that person might be offended.
那个人可能会被冒犯。

104
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Gosh.
天哪。

105
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:29,240
Or maybe if you say, I think people with brown hair are so ugly and there's someone next
或者，如果你说，我觉得棕色头发的人很丑，而旁边

106
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:31,880
to me with brown hair, they say, oh, I'm offended.
就有一个棕色头发的人，他们会说，哦，我被冒犯了。

107
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:32,880
Right.
对。

108
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:34,640
I'm not ugly, but I have brown hair.
我不丑，但我有棕色头发。

109
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,640
That's right.
没错。

110
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:40,880
Okay, so you don't want to offend anyone by being too direct or you don't want to have
好的，所以你不想因为太直接而冒犯任何人，或者你不想让

111
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:43,360
anyone feel offended.
任何人感到被冒犯。

112
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:50,440
Now for our last phrase here on Language Takeaway, we have towards the end of the dialogue, Tracy
现在，在“语言小贴士”的最后一个短语中，在对话的结尾，Tracy

113
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:54,200
thanks Melanie by saying, you are a lifesaver.
感谢Melanie时说，“你真是我的救星。”

114
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,200
Thank you.
谢谢。

115
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,680
Okay, so don't be confused.
好的，所以别搞混了。

116
00:05:56,680 --> 00:06:01,280
There is also a candy called lifesavers and she's not calling her a candy.
还有一种糖果叫“救生圈”，她不是在叫她糖果。

117
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,640
She's saying, wow, thank you.
她说的是，哇，谢谢你。

118
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,880
You really helped me.
你真的帮了我大忙。

119
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,920
So when someone helps you a lot, you can call them a lifesaver.
所以当有人帮了你大忙时，你可以叫他们“救星”。

120
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:11,880
Marco, what exactly is the object, the lifesaver?
Marco，“救星”这个东西到底是什么？

121
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:19,520
If you've ever been on a boat, you see this big orange circle that is used to throw into
如果你坐过船，你会看到那个用来扔进

122
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:22,480
the water to help someone to prevent them from drowning.
水里帮助别人防止溺水的大橙色圆圈。

123
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,080
That is called a lifesaver.
那东西就叫“救生圈”。

124
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,920
Okay, so I'm drowning.
好的，所以我快淹死了。

125
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,840
I'm having a hard time writing this email.
我写这封邮件很费劲。

126
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,800
I do not know what to say.
我不知道该说什么。

127
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,200
Marco, you come and help me.
Marco，你来帮我。

128
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,000
I can say, oh wow, thank you so much.
我可以说，哦哇，太感谢你了。

129
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,320
You're a lifesaver.
你真是我的救星。

130
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,880
That's exactly right.
完全正确。

131
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:39,520
All right, so we've taken a look at five key words there.
好了，我们看了五个关键词。

132
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:45,160
Why don't we take a listen to our dialogue again and we'll be back with Fluency Builder.
我们再来听一遍对话，然后回来讲“流利度训练”。

133
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:53,400
Melanie, can you help me with something?
Melanie，你能帮我个忙吗？

134
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:58,160
We need to finalize the account with the Mexican embassy and I need some advice on phrasing
我们需要敲定与墨西哥大使馆的账目，我需要一些关于如何用英语

135
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,880
this letter correctly in English.
正确措辞这封信的建议。

136
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:05,960
Sure Tracy, let me just get my laptop.
当然Tracy，让我拿一下我的笔记本电脑。

137
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:13,240
Right, all set.
好了，准备好了。

138
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:18,880
Okay, so to whom it may concern, I am writing...
好的，那么“敬启者，我写信是为了……”

139
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:22,560
Tracy, I think that's a little too formal.
Tracy，我觉得那有点太正式了。

140
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:27,240
I know you want to be polite, but you've already made contact with them, so in English, you
我知道你想礼貌，但你已经和他们联系过了，所以在英语里，你

141
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,600
can be a bit more relaxed in the opening.
可以在开头稍微放松一点。

142
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,520
Okay, more relaxed.
好的，放松一点。

143
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,520
Got it.
明白了。

144
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,080
Hey Sally, what's up?
嘿Sally，最近怎么样？

145
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:35,960
It's Tracy here, just...
我是Tracy，只是……

146
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:39,960
Okay Tracy, now it's too relaxed.
好了Tracy，现在又太随意了。

147
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:42,120
You've still got to show some respect.
你还是得表现出一些尊重。

148
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:45,600
How about starting with, dear Miss Cooper, I'm writing to confirm...
以“亲爱的Cooper小姐，我写信是为了确认……”开头怎么样？

149
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,840
Great, okay.
太好了，好的。

150
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:57,040
Dear Miss Cooper, I'm writing to confirm the final quotation for the full-page back cover
亲爱的Cooper小姐，我写信是为了确认您为《Viola》杂志春季刊

151
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:05,120
color advertisement you requested for the spring issue of Viola Magazine.
要求的全页封底彩色广告的最终报价。

152
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,480
That's great.
太好了。

153
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:17,320
The final costing, including advert design and production, comes to 45,600 RMB.
最终成本，包括广告设计和制作，是45,600元人民币。

154
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:24,880
We want payment 10 working days before publication, or we will cancel the ad.
我们要求在出版前10个工作日付款，否则我们将取消广告。

155
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:25,880
Thanks for...
感谢……

156
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:29,560
Whoa, okay, back up a second Tracy.
哇，好了，先停一下Tracy。

157
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,160
That's too direct.
那太直接了。

158
